{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make the Industrial Strategy Advisory Council a Statutory Body",
        "additional_details": "While we welcome the Government\u2019s new Industrial Strategy (2025) and its identification of key growth sectors, we think effective delivery requires stronger governance, clearer sectoral focus, and long-term coordination across skills, energy, infrastructure, and innovation policy.  We think a reformed ISAC must be empowered and have interdepartmental support to provide that as compared with Japan's Ministry of International Trade and Industry.",
        "background": "Reform the ISAC into a statutory body with legal powers to enforce and coordinate skills, energy, infrastructure, and innovation across key sectors, and lead a unified public\u2013private industrial roadmapping process with leading industrial experts with updates to drive long-term economic growth.",
